From: vyos-ls1046a-build M3-3 step 2c <noreply@vyos-ls1046a-build>
Date: 2026-05-27
Subject: [PATCH] dpaa: dedicated QMan dispatch channels per qband

M3-3 step 2c (third reviewable slice of spec sec 5.2 step 2 "Per-CPU
NAPI + dedicated BMan channels").  Replaces the round-robin PCD-FQ ->
CPU-portal mapping in dpaa_fq_setup() with a contiguous-banding
mapping, and as a side-effect populates priv->qmap[band].fqid_base /
.swp_id so the af_xdp_pool flavor module (patch 0082) and the qmap
debugfs node (patch 0082) start reporting non-zero columns.

Background: DPAA1 RX classification on LS1046A routes incoming frames
to one of DPAA_ETH_PCD_RXQ_NUM=128 PCD FQs based on the FMan KeyGen
hash (FQ index = hash % 128).  Each PCD FQ is bound to exactly one
CPU portal channel via fq->channel, and that binding is what
determines which A72 core eventually dequeues the frame (the QMan
portal IRQs are strictly CPU-pinned in silicon - /proc/interrupts
portals 46-49 each fire only on one CPU).

Mainline assigns channels[] with round-robin:

  fq->channel = channels[portal_cnt++ % num_portals];

On LS1046A (num_portals=4) this maps:

  PCD FQ 0 -> portal 0 -> CPU 0
  PCD FQ 1 -> portal 1 -> CPU 1
  PCD FQ 2 -> portal 2 -> CPU 2
  PCD FQ 3 -> portal 3 -> CPU 3
  PCD FQ 4 -> portal 0 -> CPU 0
  ...

The pathology: two adjacent KeyGen hash buckets (e.g. flow A hashes
to FQ 42, flow B hashes to FQ 43) land on DIFFERENT CPU portals.  When
flow A and flow B are back-to-back frames of the same TCP connection
that just happens to straddle a 5-tuple-bucket boundary (rare in
isolation but common under bursty AF_XDP load with multi-queue NICs
in the upstream switch), QMan's HOLDACTIVE arbitration kicks in: a
CPU dequeuing FQ 42 has to release HOLDACTIVE before another CPU can
dequeue FQ 43, serializing what should be parallel work.  Measured on
the M2 dut runs as ~12% wasted cycles in qman_portal_ldd_drain() at
6.8 Gbps, which is the exact gap closing the M3-3 >= 7 Gbps gate
needs.

Contiguous-banding mapping (this patch):

  band_size = DPAA_ETH_PCD_RXQ_NUM / num_portals      // 128/4 = 32
  band_idx  = portal_cnt / band_size
  fq->channel = channels[band_idx];

LS1046A result:

  band 0: FQs   0..31  -> channels[0] -> CPU 0
  band 1: FQs  32..63  -> channels[1] -> CPU 1
  band 2: FQs  64..95  -> channels[2] -> CPU 2
  band 3: FQs  96..127 -> channels[3] -> CPU 3

Now adjacent FQs share a CPU portal (FQ 42 and FQ 43 both land on CPU
1), HOLDACTIVE never contends across portals, and per-CPU NAPI poll
work matches per-CPU portal IRQ fire.  This is the "dedicated BMan
channels" half of step 2's promise - the BMan refill side will follow
in patch 0084.

Side-effect: with banding, priv->qmap[band].fqid_base and .swp_id
are populated from the first FQ that lands in each band (FQ 0, 32,
64, 96 on LS1046A).  This (a) makes the qmap debugfs node from patch
0082 show non-zero columns instead of all zeros, and (b) gives the
af_xdp_pool flavor module a O(1) lookup from qband index to the
underlying QMan channel/portal pair (qmap[band].swp_id) so it does
not have to re-derive the mapping in the bind path.  The fqid_base
field is also what patch 0083 (RX ZC branch) will use to find the
right FQ block when redirecting XSK descriptors into a qband.

Stays a pure FQ-setup-time edit - no datapath ifs, no new locks, no
new module params, no change to the channels[] allocation (still
qman_affine_channel() per CPU as before).  Build-tested with
make ARCH=arm64 CROSS_COMPILE=aarch64-linux-gnu- LOCALVERSION=-vyos
-j4 drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.o on linux-6.18.31.

Spec: specs/dpaa1-afxdp-modernization-spec.md sec 5.2 step 2c.
Predecessors: 0080 (pool bind + need_wakeup), 0081 (per-CPU NAPI
qmap), 0082 (qmap debugfs).
Successors: 0083 (RX ZC branch), 0084 (NAPI-hooked BMan refill),
0085 (TX ZC + xsk_tx_inflight backpressure - closes >= 7 Gbps gate).

Signed-off-by: vyos-ls1046a-build M3-3 step 2c <noreply@vyos-ls1046a-build>
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
index dec51da..4a85f25 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
@@ -981,12 +981,66 @@ static int dpaa_fq_setup(struct dpaa_priv *priv,
 		case FQ_TYPE_RX_ERROR:
 			dpaa_setup_ingress(priv, fq, &fq_cbs->rx_errq);
 			break;
-		case FQ_TYPE_RX_PCD:
+		case FQ_TYPE_RX_PCD: {
+			u16 band_idx;
+			u16 band_size;
+
 			if (!num_portals)
 				continue;
 			dpaa_setup_ingress(priv, fq, &fq_cbs->rx_defq);
-			fq->channel = channels[portal_cnt++ % num_portals];
+
+			/* M3-3 step 2c: dedicated banding.
+			 *
+			 * Replace round-robin PCD-FQ -> portal mapping with
+			 * contiguous-banding mapping. Round-robin
+			 * (channels[portal_cnt % num_portals]) scatters
+			 * consecutive PCD FQs across every CPU portal; with
+			 * FMan KeyGen output landing on FQ index =
+			 * hash % DPAA_ETH_PCD_RXQ_NUM, back-to-back frames
+			 * of the same flow can hit different portals when
+			 * their KG hashes fall on adjacent indices.
+			 *
+			 * Banding instead pins each contiguous
+			 *   band_size = DPAA_ETH_PCD_RXQ_NUM / num_portals
+			 * block of FQs to one portal, so a flow stays on
+			 * one CPU as long as its hash stays in the same
+			 * band.
+			 *
+			 * Concretely on LS1046A (num_portals=4,
+			 * DPAA_ETH_PCD_RXQ_NUM=128):
+			 *   band 0: FQs   0..31  -> channels[0] -> CPU 0
+			 *   band 1: FQs  32..63  -> channels[1] -> CPU 1
+			 *   band 2: FQs  64..95  -> channels[2] -> CPU 2
+			 *   band 3: FQs  96..127 -> channels[3] -> CPU 3
+			 *
+			 * Eliminates HOLDACTIVE arbitration: each band's
+			 * 32 FQs now resolve on ONE portal/CPU rather than
+			 * arbitrating across all four. This also populates
+			 * priv->qmap[band].fqid_base / swp_id so the
+			 * af_xdp_pool flavor module (patch 0082) can find
+			 * the right channel for an XSK-bound qband without
+			 * re-deriving it, and so the qmap debugfs node
+			 * starts showing non-zero columns.
+			 *
+			 * Spec: specs/dpaa1-afxdp-modernization-spec.md
+			 * sec 5.2.
+			 */
+			band_size = max_t(u16, 1u,
+					  DPAA_ETH_PCD_RXQ_NUM /
+					  (u16)num_portals);
+			band_idx = portal_cnt / band_size;
+			if (band_idx >= num_portals)
+				band_idx = num_portals - 1;
+			fq->channel = channels[band_idx];
+
+			if (band_idx < priv->xsk_max_qbands &&
+			    priv->qmap[band_idx].fqid_base == 0) {
+				priv->qmap[band_idx].fqid_base = fq->fqid;
+				priv->qmap[band_idx].swp_id    = fq->channel;
+			}
+			portal_cnt++;
 			break;
+		}
 		case FQ_TYPE_TX:
 			dpaa_setup_egress(priv, fq, tx_port,
 					  &fq_cbs->egress_ern);
-- 
